between 1st and 3d semicolons, less 47 words after 1st semicolon, and less 72 words before 3d semicolon, of 1st sentence); added "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-04/ch227/s34"},"text":"June 4, 1920, ch. 227, § 34","children":[],"tail":" (words between 1st and 3d semicolons, less 47 words after 1st semicolon, and less 72 words before 3d semicolon, of 1st sentence of last par.), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/779"},"text":"41 Stat. 779","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-03-09/ch161"},"text":"Mar. 9, 1928, ch. 161","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/251"},"text":"45 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the introductory clause is inserted for clarity. The words “at the option of the Secretary of the Army” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “of the actual performance of the same” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (c) is substituted for the words “the most usual and direct route within such limits as to territory as the Secretary of the Army may prescribe * * * for the distance by the shortest usually traveled route from the places from which they are authorized to proceed to the camp, and for the return travel thereto”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab7be425-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab7be426-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"te